w.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/27192558/how-greatest-odi-finish-played-out|title=Nerve, skill, errors: How the greatest ODI finish played out|work=ESPNCricinfo|date=15 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! Bowler\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{flagicon|NZ}} [[Trent Boult]]\n|-\n!align=center| Ball\n! Batsman !! Outcome\n|-\n!align=center| 1\n| [[Ben Stokes]] || 3\n|-\n!align=center| 2\n| [[Jos Buttler]] || 1\n|-\n!align=center| 3\n| Ben Stokes || '''4'''\n|-\n!align=center| 4\n| Ben Stokes || 1\n|-\n!align=center| 5\n| Jos Buttler || 2\n|-\n!align=center| 6\n| Jos Buttler || '''4'''\n|-\n!align=center| ''Total''\n|colspan=\"2\"| 15/0\n|}\n{{col-break}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"| {{cr|NZ}} Super Over<ref name=\"FINAL SO\"/>\n|-\n! Bowler\n|colspan=\"2\"| {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jofra Archer]]\n|-\n!align=center| Ball\n! Batsman !! Outcome\n|-\n!align=center| 1\n| [[James Neesham]] || [[Wide (cricket)|Wide]]\n|-\n!align=center| 2\n| James Neesham || 2\n|-\n!align=center| 3\n| James Neesham || '''6'''\n|-\n!align=center| 4\n| James Neesham || 2\n|-\n!align=center| 5\n| James Neesham || 2\n|-\n!align=center| 6\n| James Neesham || 1\n|-\n!align=center| 7\n| [[Martin Guptill]] || 1 and '''W'''<br>run out ([[Jason Roy]]/[[Jos Buttler]])\n|-\n!align=center| ''Total''\n|colspan=\"2\"| 15/1\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n{{Hidden end}}\n\n==Post-match==\n===Reaction===\n[[File:Lord's Cricket Stadium Panoramic.jpg|thumb|center|750px|Panoramic view of Lord's, where the final took place.]]\n[[File:Icc cricket world cup trophy.jpg|upright|thumb|The [[Cricket World Cup Trophy]], which was awarded to England after the 2019 final.]]\nThe closeness of the match, with scores being level even after the end of the Super Over and England claiming the tie-breaker by having scored more boundaries throughout the match, combined with the dramatic turn of events in the final hour and the fact that it was played as a Cricket World Cup Final, led to many former and active players, analysts and media outlets describing it as the greatest cricket match ever played.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/27191037/the-best-white-ball-game-all |title='The best white-ball game of all time!' |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref> Former England one-day bowler [[Stuart Broad]] called it \"the best white ball game of all time\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/firstcricket/sports-news/new-zealand-vs-england-icc-cricket-world-cup-2019-the-best-white-ball-game-of-all-time-twitter-is-thrilled-after-dramatic-finale-6992611.html |title=New Zealand vs England, ICC Cricket World Cup 2019: 'The best white ball game of all-time', Twitter is thrilled after dramatic finale- Firstcricket News, Firstpost}}</ref> England players Joe Root and Jonny Bairstow declared the World Cup Final as \"the greatest game ever\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/cricket/england/cricket-world-cup/news/joe-root-jonny-bairstow-declare-world-cup-final-as-the-greatest-game-ever_365075.html |title=Joe Root, Jonny Bairstow declare World Cup final as the greatest game ever}}</ref> \n\n''[[The Guardian]]''{{'}}s live commentator wrote: \"That is the most amazing game I have ever seen in my life.\"<ref name=\"TossUn\"/> ''[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]'' called it \"one of the most dramatic clashes in cricket history\",<ref>{{Cite web |first=Jon |last=Pierik |title=Greatest finish ever: England win World Cup on countback in Super Over thriller |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/cricket/44-year-wait-over-england-topple-new-zealand-to-become-world-champions-20190714-p52756.html |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=14 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019 }}</ref> while ''[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]]'' referred to it as \"the greatest ODI ever played\".<ref>{{Cite web |first=Geoff |last=Lemon |title=It was clear in every moment: We've just seen the greatest ODI ever played |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-07-15/cricket-world-cup-final-was-the-greatest-odi-ever-played/11308764 |publisher=ABC News |date=14 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019 }}</ref> The headline of ''[[The Week]]'' was \"Super human Ben Stokes drags England to victory in the greatest cricket match\".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Super human Ben Stokes drags England to victory in the greatest cricket match |url=https://www.theweek.co.uk/cricket/102260/super-human-ben-stokes-drags-england-to-victory-in-the-greatest-cricket-match |work=The Week |date=15 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019 }}</ref> With [[Novak Djokovic]] and [[Roger Federer]] contesting the [[The Championships, Wimbledon|Wimbledon Championships]]' [[2019 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles final|longest ever singles final]] (which finished during the World Cup Final), and [[Lewis Hamilton]] winning the [[British Grand Prix]] on the same day, it was referred to as a \"golden sporting Sunday\".<ref>{{Cite news |first=Richard |last=Williams |title=A golden sporting Sunday to make Britain appreciate its better self |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jul/15/sporting-sunday-britain-olympic-spirit-2012-cricket-world-cup |newspaper=The Guardian |date=15 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019 }}</ref>\n\nUmpire Kumar Dharmasena's decision to award England six runs following an overthrow boundary in the final over was criticised by former international umpire [[Simon Taufel]], who said it was an \"error in judgment\" and a \"clear mistake\" by the on-field umpires.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Clear mistake: Simon Taufel on overthrow incident in World Cup final |url=https://www.thestatesman.com/2019-cricket-world-cup/clear-mistake-simon-taufel-overthrow-incident-world-cup-final-1502777996.html |newspaper=The Statesman |date=15 July 2019}}</ref> Law 19.8 of the [[Laws of Cricket]] says \"If the boundary results from an overthrow or from the wilful act of a fielder, the runs scored shall be: any runs for penalties awarded to either side; the allowance for the boundary; and the runs completed by the batsmen, together with the run in progress if they had already crossed at the instant of the throw or act.\" As Stokes and [[Adil Rashid]] had not crossed at the moment the New Zealand fielder threw the ball, it was suggested that England should only have been awarded one completed run in addition to the overthrow boundary.<ref>{{Cite web |title=England Cricket World Cup win: 'Extra run' claims brushed off by Ashley Giles |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/48991962 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=15 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019 }}</ref> Dharmasena later admitted this was an error, though said he would \"never regret the decision\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=12251485 |title=2019 Cricket World Cup: Umpire Kumar Dharmasena admits he made a crucial mistake in final |publisher=New Zealand Herald |date=21 July 2019 |accessdate=21 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/27232695/i-never-regret-decision-kumar-dharmasena |title='I will never regret the decision' - Kumar Dharmasena |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |accessdate=21 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/kumar-dharmasena-makes-shocking-comment-umpiring-mistake-world-cup-final-802074 |title=Kumar Dharmasena makes shocking comment on umpiring mistake in World Cup final |publisher=International Business Times |first=Akshay |last=Saraswat |date=21 July 2019 |accessdate=21 July 2019 }}</ref> As a result of the incident, the [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] said it would review the overthrow rule.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/sports/cricket-world-cup-2019/story/martin-guptill-overthrow-ben-stokes-england-vs-new-zealand-world-cup-2019-final-mcc-review-rules-1571500-2019-07-20 |title=MCC to review overthrow rules after Guptill-Stokes World Cup 2019 final incident |publisher=India Today |date=20 July 2019 |accessdate=21 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/overthrow-law-to-be-reviewed-after-world-cup-final-controversy-sg3vwzfdt |title=Overthrow law to be reviewed after World Cup final controversy |publisher=[[The Times]] |first1=Matt |last1=Hughes |first2=Elizabeth |last2=Ammon |date=20 July 2019 |accessdate=21 July 2019 }}</ref> Some active and former players criticised the ICC rule of boundary count and not using the wicket count for a tied match.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/former-players-slam-icc-for-ridiculous-boundary-count-rule-that-decided-wc-winner-119071500362_1.html|title=Former players slam ICC for ridiculous boundary count rule|date=|work=Business Standard|access-date=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Jacinda Ardern]], Prime Minister of New Zealand, said that despite the loss she felt \"incredibly proud of the Black Caps, and I hope every New Zealander does because they played remarkable cricket\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-48986469 |title=Cricket World Cup: NZ PM Ardern jokes about cricket defeat 'trauma' |work=BBC News |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref> The New Zealand cricket coach, [[Gary Stead]], said that sharing the World Cup is something that \"should be considered\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/27196320/sharing-world-cup-considered-new-zealand-coach |title=Sharing World Cup 'something that should be considered' - New Zealand coach |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn the wake of the result of the final, the [[International Cricket Council|ICC]] scrapped the boundary count rule; instead teams will play as many as super overs as are necessary until the one team wins.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/cricket/icc-scraps-boundary-count-rule-that-decided-2019-world-cup/story-HlYCwmanGawwfkOsHbJUaM.html|title=After World Cup furore, ICC scraps boundary count rule|date=2019-10-14|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n===Celebrations===\n[[File:Englandvictorylap.png|thumb|left|England perform a lap of honour around Lord's after their victory.]]\nIn the wake of England's victory, the nation erupted into a state of national pride and celebrations that lasted into the night and most of the next day. The England team stayed at Lord's for most of the night celebrating. The next day, the team hosted an event at [[The Oval]], inviting fans to meet and greet the team, and pose and take photos with the trophy.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Burnton |first1=Simon |title=An all-time-classic': England celebrates Cricket World Cup victory \u2013 as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2019/jul/15/england-cricket-world-cup-final-reaction-new-zealand-live |website=The Guardian |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nQueen [[Elizabeth II]] congratulated the England team on the victory, as well as many other high-profile celebrities.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Elizabeth II |author-link=Elizabeth II |user=RoyalFamily |number=1150492172954820609 |date=14 July 2019 |title=A message from Her Majesty The Queen: Prince Philip and I send our warmest congratulations to the England Men's Cricket team after such a thrilling victory in today\u2019s World Cup Final.\" (1/2) #CricketWorldCup |access-date=16 July 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Afzal |first1=Asfia |title=Here's what celebs had to say after England won the World Cup after nail-biting final |url=https://www.brecorder.com/2019/07/15/509838/heres-what-celebs-had-to-say-after-england-won-world-cup-after-nail-biting-final/ |website=Business recorder |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n{{Cquote|Prince Philip and I send our warmest congratulations to the England Men\u2019s Cricket team after such a thrilling victory in today\u2019s World Cup Final.}}\n\nBritish Prime Minister [[Theresa May]] invited the England team to [[10 Downing Street]] the day after the victory to celebrate and offer her congratulations. Former Conservative Prime Minister [[John Major|Sir John Major]], himself a former [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey CCC]] President and honorary life Vice-President, was also in attendance.<ref>{{cite web |title=Cricket World Cup: England meet Prime Minister Theresa May at 10 Downing Street |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/48997825 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=15 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019 }}</ref> In December, Stokes was also named [[BBC Sports Personality of the Year]], making him the first cricketer to win it since [[Andrew Flintoff]] in 2005. In the subsequent New Year's Honours List, six England players and staff received [[Order of the British Empire]] decorations: CBEs for Morgan and ECB chairman Colin Graves, OBEs for Stokes and coach Trevor Bayliss and MBEs for Buttler and Root.<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/sport/50918896 New Year Honours: Eoin Morgan, Ben Stokes and Baroness Sue Campbell recognised] BBC Sport</ref>\n\n===Broadcast===\nThe match was the first international cricket match to be broadcast on free-to-air TV in the United Kingdom since the 2005 Ashes series. 8.3&nbsp;million viewers tuned in to see the final, making it one of the most viewed broadcasts of the year, with the highest audience share since the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Croatia vs England|2018 FIFA World Cup semi-Final between Croatia and England]] and the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in London.<ref>{{cite web |first=Steven |last=Impey |title=Cricket World Cup final hits 8m viewership peak |url=http://www.sportspromedia.com/news/cricket-world-cup-final-channel-4-sky-tv-viewership-f1-wimbledon |website=SportsPro |accessdate=23 August 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cricketworldcup.com Official 2019 World Cup site]\n*[http://www.icc-cricket.com/cricket-world-cup Cricket World Cup] at icc-cricket.com\n\n{{2019 Cricket World Cup}}\n{{Cricket World Cup}}\n{{International cricket in 2019}}\n{{Lord's}}\n\n[[Category:2019 Cricket World Cup|Final]]\n[[Category:Cricket World Cup Finals]]\n[[Category:England in international cricket]]\n[[Category:Lord's]]\n[[Category:Cricket in London]]\n[[Category:2019 sports events in London|Cricket World Cup Final]]\n", "name_user": "TheCapedCrusaderOfUtopia", "label": "safe", "comment": "Just changed a bit of the writing in the post match section", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Cricket_World_Cup_Final"}
{"title_page": "Once Upon a Time in Hollywood", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 film by Quentin Tarantino}}\n{{Use American English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Once Upon a Time in Hollywood\n| image          = Once Upon a Time in Hollywood poster.png\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Quentin Tarantino]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[David Heyman]]\n* [[Shannon McIntosh (filmmaker)|Shannon McIntosh]]\n* Quentin Tarantino\n}}\n| writer         = Quentin Tarantino\n| starring       = <!--PER BILLING BLOCK-->{{Plainlist|\n* [[Leonardo DiCaprio]]\n* [[Brad Pitt]]\n* [[Margot Robbie]]\n* [[Emile Hirsch]]\n* [[Margaret Qualley]]\n* [[Timothy Olyphant]]\n* [[Austin Butler]]\n* [[Dakota Fanning]]\n* [[Bruce Dern]]\n* [[Al Pacino]]<!--DO NOT ADD ADDITIONAL NAMES-->\n}}\n| cinematography = [[Robert Richardson (cinematographer)|Robert Richardson]]\n| editing        = [[Fred Raskin]]\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]\n* [[Polybona Films|Bona Film Group]]\n* [[Heyday Films]]\n* Visiona Romantica\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|5|21|[[2019 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|2019|7|26|United States|2019|8|14|United Kingdom}}\n| runtime        = 161 minutes<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/once-upon-time-hollywood-2019 |title=ONCE UPON A TIME IN HOLLYWOOD (18) |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |date=July 11, 2019 |accessdate=July 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711130452/https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/once-upon-time-hollywood-2019 |archive-date=July 11, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| country        = {{Plainlist|\n* United States\n* United Kingdom\n* China<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/5da789ea829e2|title=Once Upon a Time\u2026 in Hollywood (2019)|publisher=[[British Film Institute]]|access-date=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $90\u201396 million<ref name=\"opening\"/>\n| gross          = $374.3 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=untitledtarantino.htm |title=Once Upon a Time in Hollywood (2019) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]] |access-date=February 14, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830125636/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=untitledtarantino.htm |archive-date=August 30, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'''''{{efn|name=stylized|Stylized onscreen as '''''Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood''''' and in promotional materials as '''''Once Upon a Time in... Hollywood'''''}} is a 2019 <!-- DO NOT ADD OR CHANGE MORE GENRES. The film is a comedy drama film. Not crime, action or more so. Period Drama doesn't count from the reason it's an alternative history --> [[comedy-drama]] film written and directed by [[Quentin Tarantino]]. Produced by [[Columbia Pictures]], [[Bona Film Group]], [[Heyday Films]], and Visiona Romantica and distributed by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]], it is a co-production between the United States, United Kingdom and China. It features a large [[ensemble cast]] led by [[Leonardo DiCaprio]], [[Brad Pitt]], and [[Margot Robbie]]. Set in 1969 Los Angeles, the film follows an actor and his stunt double, as they navigate the changing film industry, and features \"multiple storylines in a modern fairy tale tribute to the final moments of [[Classical Hollywood cinema|Hollywood's golden age]].\"<ref name=\"synopis\">{{cite news |title=Once Upon a Time In... Hollywood Movie Synopsis {{!}} Official Website {{!}} Sony Pictures |url=https://www.onceuponatimeinhollywood.movie/synopsis/ |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |work=Once Upon a Time In... Hollywood |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322054919/https://www.onceuponatimeinhollywood.movie/synopsis/ |archive-date=March 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Olson |first1=Matthew |url=http://digg.com/2019/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-reviews-is-it-good-tarantino-dicaprio-robbie-pitt |title=Does Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time In Hollywood' Live Up To The Hype? Here's What Critics Say |publisher=Digg.com |accessdate=July 25, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724215302/http://digg.com/2019/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-reviews-is-it-good-tarantino-dicaprio-robbie-pitt |archive-date=July 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/11/quentin-tarantino-harvey-weinstein-sony-manson-movie |title=Quentin Tarantino Is Ditching Weinstein for Sony |last=Sperling |first=Nicole |date=November 17, 2017 |website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180225160449/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/11/quentin-tarantino-harvey-weinstein-sony-manson-movie|archive-date=February 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAnnounced in July 2017, it is the first Tarantino film to not involve [[Bob Weinstein|Bob]] and [[Harvey Weinstein]], as Tarantino ended his partnership with the brothers following the [[Harvey Weinstein sexual abuse cases|sexual abuse allegations against the latter]]. After a bidding war, the film was distributed by [[Sony Pictures]], which met Tarantino's demands including [[final cut privilege]]. Pitt, DiCaprio, Robbie, [[Zo\u00eb Bell]], [[Kurt Russell]], and others joined the cast between January and June 2018. [[Principal photography]] lasted from June through November around Los Angeles. It is the last film to feature [[Luke Perry]], who died in March 2019.\n\n''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' premiered at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes Film Festival]] on May 21, 2019, and was theatrically released in the United States on July 26, 2019 and in the United Kingdom on August 14. The film has grossed $374 million worldwide and received praise from critics for Tarantino's screenplay and direction, acting, cinematography, costume design, production values, and soundtrack, though it received criticism for its pacing and running time. Among its [[List of accolades received by Once Upon a Time in Hollywood|various accolades]], the film was chosen by the [[American Film Institute]] and the [[National Board of Review]] as one of the top ten films of the year. It received 10 nominations at the [[92nd Academy Awards]], including [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]], and won [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] (Pitt) and [[Academy Award for Best Production Design|Best Production Design]]. It also won [[Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture \u2013 Musical or Comedy|Best Motion Picture \u2013 Musical or Comedy]] at the [[77th Golden Globe Awards]].\n\nA television series of ''Bounty Law'' depicted in the film is being developed by Tarantino, who has written five episodes of the series.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.esquireme.com/content/42823-quentin-tarantino-is-making-a-real-life-bounty-law-tv-show|title=Quentin Tarantino is making a real-life bounty law TV show|website=Esquire Middle East|language=en|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com.au/entertainment/film-tv/quentin-tarantino-plans-to-turn-fictional-western-bounty-law-into-a-real-series/news-story/a2e81c7d1d29df7e5782eb19e1f2d87b|title=Quentin Tarantino Plans To Turn Fictional Western Bounty Law Into A Real Series|last=Nash|first=Brad|date=2020-01-21|website=GQ|language=en|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, plot summaries for feature films should be between 400 to 700 words only. -->\nIn February 1969, veteran [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] actor Rick Dalton (DiCaprio), star of 1950s [[Western (genre)|Western]] television series ''Bounty Law'', fears his career is waning. Casting agent Marvin Schwarz (Pacino) recommends he make [[Spaghetti Western]]s in Italy, which Dalton feels are beneath him. Dalton's best friend and [[stunt double]], Cliff Booth (Pitt)\u2014a war [[veteran]] skilled in hand-to-hand combat<ref>{{citation |title=Quentin Tarantino defends Bruce Lee scene in 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' |url=https://us.blastingnews.com/showbiz-tv/2019/08/quentin-tarantino-defends-bruce-lee-scene-in-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-002965405.html |accessdate=January 6, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191104220815/https://us.blastingnews.com/showbiz-tv/2019/08/quentin-tarantino-defends-bruce-lee-scene-in-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-002965405.html |archive-date=November 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> who lives in a tiny trailer with his [[pit bull]], Brandy\u2014drives Dalton around Los Angeles because Dalton's driver's license has been suspended due to [[DUI]]. Booth struggles to find stunt work in Hollywood because of rumors he murdered his wife. Actress [[Sharon Tate]] (Robbie) and her husband, director [[Roman Polanski]] (Zawierucha), have moved [[10050 Cielo Drive|next door to Dalton]]. He dreams of befriending them to revive his declining acting career. That night, Tate and Polanski attend a celebrity-filled party at the [[Playboy Mansion]].\n\nThe next day, while repairing Dalton's TV antenna, Booth reminisces about a [[sparring]] contest he had with [[Bruce Lee]] on the set of ''[[The Green Hornet (TV series)|The Green Hornet]]'' which resulted in Booth being fired. Meanwhile, [[Charles Manson]] (Herriman) stops by the Polanski residence looking for [[Record producer|music producer]] [[Terry Melcher]], who used to live there, but is turned away by [[Jay Sebring]] (Hirsch). Tate goes out for errands and stops at a movie theater to watch herself in the film ''[[The Wrecking Crew (1968 film)|The Wrecking Crew]]''.\n\nDalton is cast to play the villain in the pilot of ''[[Lancer (TV series)|Lancer]]'', and strikes up a conversation with his eight-year-old co-star, Trudi Fraser. Dalton struggles to remember his lines and later suffers a breakdown in his trailer. He subsequently delivers a performance that impresses Fraser and the director, [[Sam Wanamaker]], bolstering his confidence. \n\nWhile driving Dalton's car, Booth picks up a female hitchhiker named Pussycat, whom he takes to [[Spahn Ranch]], where Booth once worked on the set of ''Bounty Law.'' He takes notice of the many [[hippie]]s living there (the [[Manson Family]]). Suspecting they may be taking advantage of the ranch's owner, [[George Spahn]] (Dern), Booth insists on checking on him despite [[Lynette Fromme|\"Squeaky\" Fromme]]'s (Fanning) objections. Booth finally speaks with Spahn, who dismisses his concerns. Upon leaving, Booth discovers that [[Steve \"Clem\" Grogan]] has slashed a tire on Dalton's car; Booth beats him and forces him to change the tire. [[Tex Watson]] is summoned to deal with the situation but he arrives as Booth is driving away.\n\nAfter watching Dalton's guest performance on an episode of ''[[The F.B.I. (TV series)|The F.B.I.]]'', Schwarz books him as the lead in [[Sergio Corbucci]]'s next Spaghetti Western, ''Nebraska Jim''. Dalton takes Booth with him for a six-month stint in Italy, during which he appears in two additional Westerns and a [[Eurospy film|Eurospy]] comedy, and marries Italian starlet Francesca Capucci. With a new wife, Dalton informs Booth he can no longer afford his services.\n\nOn the evening of August 8, 1969, their first day back in Los Angeles, Dalton and Booth go out for drinks to commemorate their time working together and then return to Dalton's house. Tate and Sebring go out for dinner with friends and then return to Tate's house. Booth smokes an [[Lysergic acid diethylamide|acid]]-laced cigarette given to him by Pussycat and takes Brandy for a walk while Dalton prepares drinks. Manson Family members Tex, [[Susan Atkins|Sadie]], [[Linda Kasabian|Flower Child]], and [[Patricia Krenwinkel|Katie]] arrive outside in preparation to [[Tate\u2013LaBianca murders|murder everyone in Tate's house]]. Dalton hears the car and orders them to get off his street. [[Alternate history|Changing their plans]], the Manson Family members decide to instead kill Dalton after Sadie reasons that Hollywood has \"taught them to murder.\" Flower Child deserts the group, speeding off with their car. They break into Dalton's house and confront Capucci and Booth, who recognizes them from his visit to Spahn Ranch. Booth orders Brandy to attack, and together they kill Katie and Tex and injure Sadie, though Booth is stabbed and knocked unconscious in the altercation. Sadie stumbles outside, alarming Dalton, who is in his pool listening to music on headphones, oblivious to the mayhem. Dalton retrieves a flamethrower that he had previously used in a movie and incinerates Sadie. After Booth is taken to the hospital to treat his injuries, Sebring engages Dalton in conversation outside and Dalton receives an invitation to have a drink with Tate and her friends at her house, which he accepts.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{cast list|\n* [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] as Rick Dalton\n* [[Brad Pitt]] as Cliff Booth\n* [[Margot Robbie]] as [[Sharon Tate]]\n* [[Emile Hirsch]] as [[Jay Sebring]]\n* [[Margaret Qualley]] as \"Pussycat\"\n* [[Timothy Olyphant]] as [[James Stacy]]\n* [[Julia Butters]] as Trudi Fraser\n* [[Austin Butler]] as \"[[Tex Watson|Tex]]\"\n* [[Dakota Fanning]] as \"[[Lynette Fromme|Squeaky]]\"\n* [[Bruce Dern]] as [[George Spahn]]\n* [[Mike Moh]] as [[Bruce Lee]]\n* [[Luke Perry]] as [[Wayne Maunder]]\n* [[Damian Lewis]] as [[Steve McQueen]]\n* [[Al Pacino]] as Marvin Schwarz\n* [[Nicholas Hammond]] as [[Sam Wanamaker]]\n* [[Samantha Robinson (American actress)|Samantha Robinson]] as [[Abigail Folger]]\n* [[Rafa\u0142 Zawierucha]] as [[Roman Polanski]]\n* [[Lorenza Izzo]] as Francesca Capucci\n* [[Costa Ronin]] as [[Wojciech Frykowski]]\n* [[Damon Herriman]] as [[Charles Manson|Charlie]]\n* [[Lena Dunham]] as \"[[Catherine Share|Gypsy]]\"\n* [[Madisen Beaty]] as \"[[Patricia Krenwinkel|Katie]]\"\n* [[Mikey Madison]] as \"[[Susan Atkins|Sadie]]\"\n* James Landry H\u00e9bert as \"[[Steve \"Clem\" Grogan|Clem]]\"\n* [[Maya Hawke]] as \"[[Linda Kasabian|Flower Child]]\"\n* [[Victoria Pedretti]] as \"[[Leslie Van Houten|Lulu]]\"\n* [[Sydney Sweeney]] as \"[[:de:Diane Lake|Snake]]\"\n* [[Harley Quinn Smith]] as \"Froggie\"\n* Dallas Jay Hunter as \"Delilah\"\n* [[Kansas Bowling]] as \"[[Sandra Good|Blue]]\"\n* Parker Love Bowling as \"Tadpole\"\n* Cassidy Vick Hice as \"Sundance\"\n* Ruby Rose Skotchdopole as \"Butterfly\"\n* [[Danielle Harris]] as \"Angel\"\n* Josephine Valentina Clark as \"Happy Cappy\"\n* [[Scoot McNairy]] as \"Business\" Bob Gilbert on ''[[Lancer (TV series)|Lancer]]''\n* [[Clifton Collins Jr.]] as Ernesto \"The Mexican\" Vaquero on ''Lancer''\n* [[Marco Rodr\u00edguez (actor)|Marco Rodr\u00edguez]] as the [[bartender]] on ''Lancer''\n* [[Ram\u00f3n Franco (actor)|Ram\u00f3n Franco]] as a Land Pirate on ''Lancer'' and Rub\u00e9n, the [[Bruin Theater]] manager\n* Raul Cardona as \"Bad Guy\" Delgado on ''Lancer''\n* Courtney Hoffman as Rebekka\n* [[Dreama Walker]] as [[Connie Stevens]]\n* Rachel Redleaf as [[Cass Elliot|Mama Cass]]\n* [[Rebecca Rittenhouse]] as [[Michelle Phillips]]\n* [[Rumer Willis]] as [[Joanna Pettet]]\n* [[Spencer Garrett]] as Allen Kincade\n* [[Clu Gulager]] as the Larry Edmunds Bookshop owner\n* [[Martin Kove]] as a ''Bounty Law'' Sheriff\n* [[Rebecca Gayheart]] as Billie Booth\n* [[Kurt Russell]] as Randy Miller and the narrator\n* [[Zo\u00eb Bell]] as Janet Miller\n* [[Michael Madsen]] as Sheriff Hackett on ''Bounty Law''\n* [[Perla Haney-Jardine]] as a hippie drug dealer\n* [[James Remar]] as \"Ugly Owl\" Hoot on ''Bounty Law''\n* [[Monica Staggs]] as Connie\n* [[Omar Doom]] as Donnie\n* [[Kate Berlant]] as the Bruin Theater ticket booth attendant\n* [[Brenda Vaccaro]] as Mary Alice Schwarz\n* [[Daniella Pick]] as Daphna Ben-Cobo\n* Tom Hartig as [[Altamont Free Concert|Bill \"Sweet William\" Fritsch]]\n* [[David Steen (actor)|David Steen]] as Straight Satan David\n* [[Corey Burton]] as the ''Bounty Law'' promo announcer\n* [[Toni Basil]] as a dancer on the plane during the opening credits sequence<ref name=toni-basil>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/06/arts/dance/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-tarantino-toni-basil.html |title=Quentin Tarantino's Goddess of Go-Go |first=Debra |last=Levine |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=August 6, 2019 |accessdate=August 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806163003/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/06/arts/dance/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-tarantino-toni-basil.html |archive-date=August 6, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Rage Stewart as [[KHJ (AM)|Harvey \"Humble Harve\" Miller]]\n* [[Quentin Tarantino]] as the offscreen director of the Red Apple cigarettes TV commercial. He can be heard announcing the title of ''Bounty Law''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Rybov |first=Eugene |url=https://invidious.13ad.de/watch?v=Ec5em1mqJtQ |title=Special interview with Quentin Tarantino for OK about 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' |website=invidious |access-date=August 26, 2019 |date=August 11, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Maurice Compte]], [[Vincent Laresca]], [[Lew Temple]], Craig Stark, [[JLouis Mills]], Eddie Perez, Gilbert Saldivar, and Keith Jefferson as the other Land Pirates on ''Lancer''.\n* [[James Marsden]] as [[Burt Reynolds]] (extended release)\n* [[Walton Goggins]] as the voice of Old Chattanooga Beer (extended release)\n}}\n\n== Character background ==\n=== Fictional characters ===\nRick Dalton is an actor who starred in the fictitious [[Westerns on television|television western]] series ''Bounty Law'', based on the real-life series ''[[Wanted Dead or Alive (TV series)|Wanted Dead or Alive]],'' starring [[Steve McQueen]].<ref name=\"Bounty Law Wasnt a Real TV Show\">{{cite news |last=Lachenal |first=Jessica |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/bounty-law-wasnt-a-real-tv-show-but-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-borrowed-from-this-classic-series-18180457 |title=\"Bounty Law\" Wasn't A Real TV Show, But 'Once Upon A Time In Hollywood' Borrowed From This Classic Series |work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] |access-date=August 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812040954/https://www.bustle.com/p/bounty-law-wasnt-a-real-tv-show-but-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-borrowed-from-this-classic-series-18180457 |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Dalton's relationship with Cliff Booth is based on [[Burt Reynolds]]' with his longtime [[stunt double]] [[Hal Needham]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Langmann |first=Brady |url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/movies/a28504994/brad-pitt-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-character-true-story-stuntman-hal-needham/ |title=The Stuntman Who Inspired Brad Pitt's ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' Character Is More Badass In Real Life |work=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] |date=July 25, 2019 |accessdate=July 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727174410/https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/movies/a28504994/brad-pitt-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-character-true-story-stuntman-hal-needham/ |archive-date=July 27, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Dalton was inspired by actors whose careers began in [[Classical Hollywood cinema|Classical Hollywood]] but faltered in the 1960s, such as [[Ty Hardin|Ty Hardin,]] who went from starring in a successful TV western to making [[Spaghetti Western|spaghetti westerns]], as well as by [[Ralph Meeker]].<ref>{{cite podcast|url=http://thenewbev.com/blog/2019/07/pure-cinema-podcast-july-2019-with-quentin-tarantino/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722142805/http://thenewbev.com/blog/2019/07/pure-cinema-podcast-july-2019-with-quentin-tarantino/ |archivedate=July 22, 2019|date=July 3, 2019|website=Pure Cinema Podcast|title=New Beverly Calendar: July, 2019 (with Quentin Tarantino)|publisher=The New Bev|minutes=13}}</ref><ref name=\"True story characters\"/><ref name=recut>{{cite web |last=Thompson |first=May |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/05/quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-recut-longer-cannes-1202143936/ |title=Quentin Tarantino Says He May Recut 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' to Make it Longer |website=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=September 9, 2019 |date=May 23, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190529175013/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/05/quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-recut-longer-cannes-1202143936/ |archive-date=May 29, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Meeker>{{cite news |last=Hellerman |first=Jason |url=https://nofilmschool.com/Tarantino-breakdowns-character |title=How Tarantino and DiCaprio Crafted his 'Hollywood' Character |website=nofilmschool |access-date=August 28, 2019 |date=August 2, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829012156/https://nofilmschool.com/Tarantino-breakdowns-character |archive-date=August 29, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Though not mentioned in the film, Dalton apparently suffers from undiagnosed [[bipolar disorder]], inspired by [[Pete Duel]].<ref name=Bipolar>{{cite news |last=Galbraith |first=Alex |url=https://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2019/08/rick-dalton-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-bipolar |title=Tarantino on DiCaprio's 'OUATIH' Character Rick Dalton Being Bipolar: 'We Never Say the Words' |website=Complex |access-date=August 19, 2019 |date=August 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819155028/https://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2019/08/rick-dalton-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-bipolar |archive-date=August 19, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCliff Booth, Dalton's stunt double and best friend, is a [[World War II]] veteran, [[Green Berets|Green Beret]] and \"one of deadliest guys alive.\"<ref name=\"character-details\">{{cite news |last=Sharf |first=Zack |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/04/quentin-tarantino-details-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-characters-1202060562/ |title=Quentin Tarantino Drops New Details About His 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Characters |website=[[Indiewire]] |access-date=August 15, 2019 |date=April 19, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426032417/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/04/quentin-tarantino-details-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-characters-1202060562/ |archive-date=April 26, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Brad-Pitt-Fight-Ready\">{{cite news |last=Thorp |first=Charlie |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/agingwell/how-brad-pitt-got-fight-ready-for-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/ar-AAENYaD |title=How Brad Pitt Got Fight Ready For 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' |website=[[Men's Journal]] |access-date=August 15, 2019 |date=July 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811031736/https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/agingwell/how-brad-pitt-got-fight-ready-for-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/ar-AAENYaD |archive-date=August 11, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Quentin Tarantino]] and [[Brad Pitt]] modeled Booth after [[Tom Laughlin]]'s portrayal of [[Billy Jack]].<ref name=\"Crazy Coincidence\">{{cite news |last=Sharf |first=Zack |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-coincidence-hollywood-meeting-1202156536/ |title=The Crazy Coincidence that Brought Tarantino and Brad Pitt back together for 'Hollywood' |website=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=August 11, 2019 |date=July 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190720172844/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-coincidence-hollywood-meeting-1202156536/ |archive-date=July 20, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Booth is inspired by [[Gary Kent]], a stuntman for a film made at the [[Spahn Ranch]] while the [[Manson Family]] lived there,<ref name=\"Meet the Stuntman\">{{cite news |last=Orange |first=B. Alan |url=https://www.movieweb.com/danger-god-trailer/ |title=Danger God Trailer: Meet the Stuntman Who Helped Inspire Tarantino's Once Upon a Time |work=Movieweb |access-date=August 11, 2019 |date=August 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812001613/https://movieweb.com/danger-god-trailer/ |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Gene LeBell]], who worked on [[The Green Hornet (TV series)|''The Green Hornet'']] after complaints by other stuntmen that [[Bruce Lee]] was \"kicking the shit out of the stuntmen.\"<ref name=\"Debunking Mockery\">{{cite news |last=Robinson |first=Eugene S. |url=https://www.ozy.com/true/story/debunking-quentin-tarantinos-mockery-of-bruce-lee/95956 |title=Debunking Quentin Tarantino's 'Mockery' of Bruce Lee |work=[[Ozy (magazine)|Ozy]] |access-date=August 11, 2019 |date=August 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812002649/https://www.ozy.com/true/story/debunking-quentin-tarantinos-mockery-of-bruce-lee/95956 |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTrudi Fraser, the precocious child actor working on ''[[Lancer (TV series)|Lancer]]'', is inspired by an actual character from that series.<ref name=gamespot-easter-eggs>{{cite news |last=Rougeau |first=Michael |url=https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-42-easter-eggs-and-r/2900-2951/ |title=Once Upon A Time In Hollywood: 42 Easter Eggs & References You Might Have Missed |website=[[GameSpot]] |access-date=August 21, 2019 |date=July 31, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822002658/https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-42-easter-eggs-and-r/2900-2951/ |archive-date=August 22, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><!-- She was not inspired by [[Meryl Streep]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-julia-butters-interview |title=Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood: Meet the 10-Year-Old Leo Compared to a Young Meryl Streep |work=Vanity Fair}}</ref> --> Marvin Schwarz is Dalton's agent, a role that Tarantino wrote specifically for [[Al Pacino]].<ref name=al-pacino>{{cite news |last=Collis |first=Clark |url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/07/26/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-al-pacino/ |title=Quentin Tarantino was \"nervous\" about directing Al Pacino in Once Upon a Time in Hollywood |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=August 25, 2019 |date=July 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729035225/https://ew.com/movies/2019/07/26/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-al-pacino/ |archive-date=July 29, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Francesca Capucci, a starlet who marries Dalton, is influenced by 1960s Italian actresses [[Sophia Loren]] and [[Claudia Cardinale]].<ref name=\"True story characters\"/><ref name=\"lorenza izzo talks\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/lorenza-izzo-talks-cross-cultural-connections-once-upon-time-hollywood-n1034561 |title=Lorenza Izzo talks cross-cultural connections in 'Once Upon A Time ... In Hollywood' |last=Conde |first=Arturo |date=July 26, 2019 |website=[[NBC News]] |access-date=August 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806075706/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/lorenza-izzo-talks-cross-cultural-connections-once-upon-time-hollywood-n1034561 |archive-date=August 6, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Billie Booth is Cliff's wife, whose death echoes [[Natalie Wood]]'s.<ref name=\"True story characters\"/> Some roles, such as [[Zo\u00eb Bell]]'s stunt coordinator and Heba Thorisdottir's makeup artist, were portrayed by individuals who performed those jobs for the film.\n\n=== Historical characters ===\n*[[File:Sharon Tate Valley of the Dolls 1967.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Sharon Tate]], portrayed in the film by [[Margot Robbie]] and shown in a publicity photo from ''[[The Wrecking Crew (1968 film)|The Wrecking Crew]]'' (1968)|alt=]][[Sharon Tate]] was an actress married to film director [[Roman Polanski]], and is Dalton's neighbor in the film. [[Margot Robbie]] read Polanski's autobiography ''Roman by Polanski'' in preparation for the role.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sharf |first=Zack |title=Margot Robbie Didn't Consult Roman Polanski for Her Portrayal of Sharon Tate |work=[[IndieWire]] |date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=January 6, 2019 |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/12/margot-robbie-sharon-tate-prep-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-tarantino-1202024791/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205193423/https://www.indiewire.com/2018/12/margot-robbie-sharon-tate-prep-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-tarantino-1202024791/|archive-date=December 5, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Filmoria\">{{cite web |url=https://www.filmoria.co.uk/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-the-9th-film-from-quentin-tarantino-brand-new-poster/ |title=Margot Robbie as Sharon Tate in Quentin Tarantino's Once Upon A Time... in Hollywood. |website=Filmoria |date= |accessdate=March 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322180023/https://www.filmoria.co.uk/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-the-9th-film-from-quentin-tarantino-brand-new-poster/|archive-date=March 22, 2019}}</ref> Polanski's credits include ''[[Rosemary's Baby (film)|Rosemary's Baby]]'' and ''[[The Fearless Vampire Killers]]'', where he first met Tate.<ref>{{cite news |last=Alter |first=Ethan |url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-whats-real-and-fake-sharon-tate-bruce-lee-charlie-manson-230411013.html |title=From Sharon Tate and Bruce Lee to Rick Dalton and Cliff Booth, here's what's real and what's fake in 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' |website=Yahoo |access-date=August 29, 2019 |date=July 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829020022/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-whats-real-and-fake-sharon-tate-bruce-lee-charlie-manson-230411013.html |archive-date=August 29, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*[[Jay Sebring]] was Tate's friend and ex-boyfriend, and friend of Bruce Lee (whom he had helped get started in Hollywood) and [[Steve McQueen]].<ref name=\"True story characters\"/><ref name=hairdresser-bruce-lee/> Sebring and Tate attended a party at [[Mama Cass]]' house at which [[Charles Manson]] was also in attendance.<ref>{{cite news |last=Williams |first=Alex |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/21/style/charles-manson-annoying-hipster.html |title=How Charles Manson Nearly Made It in Hollywood |website=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=August 31, 2019 |date=November 21, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190901045635/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/21/style/charles-manson-annoying-hipster.html |archive-date=September 1, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*Abigail Folger, heir to the [[Folgers]] coffee fortune, and her boyfriend Wojciech Frykowski were Tate's friends.\n\n*[[James Stacy]] and Wayne Maunder were actors who starred on ''Lancer''.<ref name=\"Esq\">{{cite news |last=Coates |first=Tyler |url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/movies/g26888375/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-cast-photos/ |title=The Real-Life People Portrayed in Once Upon a Time in Hollywood |work=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]|access-date=March 23, 2019 |date=March 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322215648/https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/movies/g26888375/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-cast-photos/ |archive-date=March 22, 2019}}</ref> Stacy is last shown in the film leaving the show's set on a motorcycle; Stacy was in a motorcycle accident that resulted in the death of his passenger and the loss of his arm and leg. His ex-wife, actress [[Connie Stevens]], also portrayed in the film, organized a fundraiser for his recovery.<ref name=hitting-bottom>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20141272,00.html |title=Hitting Bottom |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |volume=45 |issue=19 |page=62 |issn=0093-7673 |access-date=August 20, 2019 |date=May 13, 1996 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923221426/http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20141272,00.html |archive-date=September 23, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"True story characters\"/> Maunder died during the filming of the movie and [[Luke Perry]], who portrays him in his last screen appearance, died shortly afterward.<ref name=luke-perry>{{cite news |last=Lawrence |first=Derek |url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/03/04/luke-perry-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/ |title=Luke Perry's final role will be in Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=August 17, 2019 |date=March 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626213157/https://ew.com/movies/2019/03/04/luke-perry-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/ |archive-date=June 26, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Luke's son, Jack Perry, appears with him in the film.<ref name=Luke-Perry's-son>{{cite news |last=Fernandez |first=Alexia |url=https://people.com/movies/luke-perry-son-jack-appearing-once-upon-time-hollywood/ |title=Luke Perry's Son Jack Will Appear with His Father in ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' |website=[[People (magazine)|People]] |access-date=August 17, 2019 |date=May 8, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510055802/https://people.com/movies/luke-perry-son-jack-appearing-once-upon-time-hollywood/ |archive-date=May 10, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Sam Wanamaker]] directed the real pilot of ''Lancer'', in which the Land Pirates were actual characters.<ref name=Lancer>{{cite web |url=http://www.westernclippings.com/remember/lancer_doyouremember.shtml |title=Lancer |website=westernclippings |access-date=August 31, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831213244/http://www.westernclippings.com/remember/lancer_doyouremember.shtml |archive-date=August 31, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Bruce Lee was an actor and martial artist who starred as [[Kato (The Green Hornet)|Kato]] on ''The Green Hornet''. He taught Tate martial arts for ''The Wrecking Crew'', and also trained Sebring, Polanski and McQueen.<ref name=hairdresser-bruce-lee>{{cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/culture/film-tv/article/2154838/bruce-lee-steve-mcqueen-and-hairdresser-killed-manson-family-who |title=Bruce Lee, Steve McQueen, and the hairdresser killed by the Manson Family who introduced the pair |website=[[South China Morning Post]] |access-date=August 18, 2019 |date=July 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818160155/https://www.scmp.com/culture/film-tv/article/2154838/bruce-lee-steve-mcqueen-and-hairdresser-killed-manson-family-who |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*\"Mama Cass\" Elliot and [[Michelle Phillips]] were members of [[the Mamas and the Papas]]. The sheet music for their song \"Straight Shooter\" was found on the piano at the murder scene inside the Tate/Polanski residence, and it is also used in the film's trailer.<ref name=straight-shooter>{{cite news |last=Runtagh |first=Jordan |url=https://people.com/music/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-trailer-chilling-musical-secret/ |title=The Once Upon a Time in Hollywood Trailer Makes a Chilling Secret Reference to Charles Manson |website=[[People (magazine)|People]] |access-date=August 19, 2019 |date=March 21, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727192158/https://people.com/music/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-trailer-chilling-musical-secret/ |archive-date=July 27, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Polanski had an affair with Phillips while he was married to Sharon Tate.<ref name=polanski-phillips>{{cite news |last=Birmingham |first=John |url=https://purpleclover.littlethings.com/entertainment/7303-hollywood-one-night-stands/item/michelle-phillips-and-roman-polanski/ |title=15 Celebrity One-Night Stands |website=purple clover |access-date=August 17, 2019 |date=November 16, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818032501/https://purpleclover.littlethings.com/entertainment/7303-hollywood-one-night-stands/item/michelle-phillips-and-roman-polanski/ |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*Harvey \"Humble Harve\" Miller was a Los Angeles [[radio personality|radio DJ]] who was convicted of killing his wife.<ref name=\"Humble Harve\">{{cite news |last=Lewis |first=Randy |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-me-humble-harve-miller-dead-20190606-story.html |title='Humble Harve,' former KHJ 'Boss Radio' DJ who killed wife dies at 84 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |access-date=August 12, 2019 |date=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716202421/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-me-humble-harve-miller-dead-20190606-story.html |archive-date=July 16, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*[[Tim Roth]] and [[Danny Strong]] shot scenes that were cut. Strong portrayed [[Dean Martin]] and Roth portrayed Amos Russell, Sebring's English butler.<ref name=How-Stars-Compare-to-Real-Life-Players>{{cite news |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1059735/margot-robbie-luke-perry-and-more-see-how-the-stars-of-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-compare-to-the-real-life-players#photo-1020682 |title=Margot Robbie, Luke Perry, and More: See How the Stars of Once Upon a Time in Hollywood Compare to the Real-Life Players |website=[[E! News]] |last=Nilles |first=Billy |access-date=August 13, 2019 |date=July 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190813203358/https://www.eonline.com/news/1059735/margot-robbie-luke-perry-and-more-see-how-the-stars-of-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-compare-to-the-real-life-players#photo-1020682 |archive-date=August 13, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Tarantino-Deadline-Interview>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-interview-leonardo-dicaprio-bradd-pitt-margot-robbie-star-trek-pulp-fiction-1202647835/ |title=Quentin Tarantino On 'Once Upon a Time,' His Vision of 'Star Trek' As 'Pulp Fiction' In Space, And Hopes To Turn Leo DiCaprio 50s Western 'Bounty Law' Into Series |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike|access-date=August 13, 2019 |date=July 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/james-marsden-cut-role-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-revealed-1202160319/ |title=James Marsden's Cut Role in 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Revealed as Meta Surprise |website=[[IndieWire]] |first=Zack |last=Sharf |date=July 23, 2019 |accessdate=August 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190803140109/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/james-marsden-cut-role-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-revealed-1202160319/ |archive-date=August 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-brandy-1202160975/ |title=The Making of 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Was a Throwback to Studios' Pre-Franchise Glory Days |website=[[IndieWire]] |first=Anne |last=Thompson |date=July 26, 2019 |accessdate=August 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727215334/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-brandy-1202160975/ |archive-date=July 27, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== The Manson Family ====\n*[[George Spahn]] was an 80-year-old nearly blind man who rented his [[Spahn Ranch|ranch]] out for westerns. The Manson Family lived on the ranch. [[Burt Reynolds]] was cast, but died before filming.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Galuppo |first1=Mia |title=Burt Reynolds Did Not Shoot Role in Quentin Tarantino's New Movie |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/burt-reynolds-did-not-shoot-role-quentin-tarantinos-new-movie-1140534 |accessdate=September 6, 2018 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906235502/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/burt-reynolds-did-not-shoot-role-quentin-tarantinos-new-movie-1140534|archive-date=September 6, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Dern\">{{cite news |last1=Fleming Jr. |first1=Mike |title=Bruce Dern Replaces His Friend Burt Reynolds in Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time in Hollywood' |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/bruce-dern-replaces-burt-reynolds-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202471986/ |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=September 27, 2018 |accessdate=October 30, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004011620/https://deadline.com/2018/09/bruce-dern-replaces-burt-reynolds-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202471986/ |archive-date=October 4, 2018}}</ref> Reynolds did a rehearsal and script reading, his last performance. After reading the script and learning that Pitt would be portraying Booth, Reynolds told Tarantino, \"You gotta have somebody say, 'You're pretty for a stunt guy.'\" The line appears in the movie, but is spoken to Booth by Bruce Lee.<ref>{{cite news |last=Fernandez |first=Alexia |url=https://people.com/movies/burt-reynolds-funny-line-brad-pitt-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood |title=Burt Reynolds Came Up with Funny 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Line About Brad Pitt Before Death |website=[[People (magazine)|People]] |access-date=August 27, 2019 |date=August 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816001211/https://people.com/movies/burt-reynolds-funny-line-brad-pitt-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/ |archive-date=August 16, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Charles Manson|Charles \"Charlie\" Manson]] was a criminal and [[cult]] leader of the [[Manson Family]], a [[commune]] based in California. Members of the Family committed nine murders in 1969.<ref name=helter-skelter/> [[Damon Herriman]], who portrays Manson, also portrays him in ''[[Mindhunter (TV series)|Mindhunter]]''.\n\n*\"Pussycat\" is a [[composite character]], with her nickname based on Kathryn Lutesinger's \"Kitty Kat\" yet modeled after [[Ruth Ann Moorehouse]]. Manson frequently sent Moorehouse into the city to lure men with money back to Spahn Ranch.<ref name=\"About the Manson Family\">{{cite news |last=Romain |first=Lindsey |url=https://www.nerdist.com/article/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-manson-family-fact-check/ |title=What Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood Gets Right About the Manson Family |work=[[Nerdist Industries|Nerdist]] |access-date=August 11, 2019 |date=July 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812003254/https://nerdist.com/article/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-manson-family-fact-check/ |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Lutesinger met Manson through her boyfriend, [[Bobby Beausoleil]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Cipriani |first=Casey |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/was-pussycat-a-real-person-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-takes-some-liberties-with-the-manson-family-18200242 |title=Was Pussycat A Real Person? 'Once Upon a Time In Hollywood' Takes Some Liberties With The Manson Family |website=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] |access-date=September 17, 2019 |date=July 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725164451/https://www.bustle.com/p/was-pussycat-a-real-person-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-takes-some-liberties-with-the-manson-family-18200242 |archive-date=July 25, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> There is someone only called Pussycat in ''The Family'' by [[Ed Sanders]]. According to those interviewed, Pussycat underwent an [[exorcism]] with Manson present. The real identity of Pussycat is never revealed.<ref name=Pussycat>{{cite book |last=Sanders |first=Ed |url=https://archive.org/details/family00sand |url-access=registration |quote=Pussycat. |title=The Family: The Story of Charles Manson's Dune Buggy Attack Battalion|access-date=August 13, 2019 |date=1971 |isbn=1-56025-396-7}}</ref>\n\n*\"Squeaky\" was [[Lynette Fromme]]'s nickname, given to her by Spahn because of the sound she made when he touched her.<ref name=nicknames/> She was Spahn's main caretaker, tending to his needs, sexual or otherwise.<ref name=\"About the Manson Family\"/>\n\n*\"Straight Satan David\" is a member of the Straight Satans Motorcycle Club, associates of the Family, who acted as their security.<ref name=helter-skelter/>\n\n*Bill \"Sweet William Tumbleweed\" Fritsch was a member of the [[Hells Angels]] and [[Diggers (theater)|Diggers]], and Manson Family associate.{{citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n\n*Connie is a [[Equestrianism|horseback-riding]] customer at Spahn Ranch. As one way of earning their keep, the Family gave horseback riding tours to people visiting the ranch.<ref name=\"About the Manson Family\"/>\n*Sean Baker, Daniel Callister, Sami Henry, Tea Jo, Riley Lucente, Harold Smith, Sarah May Sommers and Zack Whyel also play members of the Manson Family.\n*\"Tex\" was [[Tex Watson|Charles Watson]]'s nickname. Spahn gave it to him because of his Texas accent.\n*\"Sadie\" was [[Susan Atkins]]' nickname. Manson gave everyone fake IDs, and the name on Atkins' was \"Sadie Mae Glutz\". Atkins was called \"Sexy Sadie\" after a [[Sexy Sadie|track]] on [[the Beatles]]' [[The Beatles (album)|self-titled album]]<!-- The album was titled \"The Beatles\", not \"The White Album\" despite the common reference. --> that some of the Family members may have believed was about her.<ref name=helter-skelter/>\n*\"Katie\" was [[Patricia Krenwinkel]]'s nickname because of the name on her ID.<ref name=nicknames/> [[Madisen Beaty]], who portrays Krenwinkel, previously portrayed her on ''[[Aquarius (American TV series)|Aquarius]]''.\n*\"[[flower child|Flower Child]]\" was not the nickname of any member. However, the character in the film is [[Linda Kasabian]], as she was the fourth member to go to Tate's house.<ref name=\"About the Manson Family\"/>\n*\"Snake\" was [[:de:Diane Lake|Dianne Lake]]'s nickname, given to her by Manson because she rolled around in grass pretending to be a snake.\n*\"Blue\" was [[Sandra Good]]'s nickname. Manson told her, \"Woman, you're earth. I'm naming you Blue. Fix the air and the water. It's your job.\"\n*\"Gypsy\" was [[Catherine Share]]'s nickname, which she gave herself after meeting a man named Gypsy with whom she shared a birthday and whom she thought was her cosmic twin.<ref name=nicknames>{{cite web |last=Sederstrom |first=Jill |url=https://www.oxygen.com/manson-the-women/crime-time/squeaky-fromme-catherine-gypsy-share-manson-family-nicknames |title=Why Did The Manson Family Members Have Nicknames? |website=[[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] |access-date=September 12, 2019 |date=August 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190813234706/https://www.oxygen.com/manson-the-women/crime-time/squeaky-fromme-catherine-gypsy-share-manson-family-nicknames |archive-date=August 13, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Catherine Gillies was nicknamed \"Capistrano\" by Spahn, but called \"Cappy\" for short.<ref name=helter-skelter/> In the film, her name is \"Happy Cappy\".\n*\"Lulu\" was one of [[Leslie Van Houten]]'s nicknames, and \"Clem\" one of [[Steve \"Clem\" Grogan|Steve Grogan]]'s.<ref name=\"About the Manson Family\"/>\n*\"Tophat\" was an alias of Bobby Beausoleil. In his book ''[[Turn Off Your Mind]]'', [[Gary Lachman]] mentions that, \"Beausoleil had a style; a [[top hat]] that set him apart from the usual hippie fare.\"<ref>{{cite book |last=Lachman |first=Gary |title=Turn Off Your Mind: The Mystic Sixties and the Dark Side of the Age of Aquarius |publisher=Red Wheel Weiser |date=June 1, 2003 |isbn=1-934708-65-8}}</ref> Beausoleil wrote, \"I spied a felt top hat in the window of a... shop... I couldn't afford (it)... but it felt like it had been made for me... I couldn't resist the temptation to buy it.\" Beausoleil claimed that as soon as he put on the hat, ideas floating in his head came together.<ref>{{cite web |last=BeauSoleil |first=Bobby |url=http://bobbybeausoleil.com/the-orkustra-notes-from-the-psychedelic-underground.html |title=The Orkusta: Notes from the Psychedelic Underground |website=bobbybeausoleil |access-date=September 12, 2019 |year=2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828203557/http://www.bobbybeausoleil.com/the-orkustra-notes-from-the-psychedelic-underground.html |archive-date=August 28, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*The character of \"Sundance\" was named by Cassidy Hice, the actress who portrays her. She wrote, \"I was asked to name my character by Quentin himself.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Hice |first=Cassidy |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0Z_X_DJV4V/ |title=Spahn Ranch |website=[[Instagram]]| access-date=September 12, 2019 |date=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n=== Writing and development ===\nThe work that would become the screenplay for ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' was developed slowly over several years by Tarantino. While he knew he wanted the work to be titled ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'', evoking the idea of a fairy tale set in 1960s Hollywood, he publicly referred to the project as ''Magnum Opus''.<ref name=\"esquire may2019\">{{cite magazine | url = https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/movies/a27458589/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-leonardo-dicaprio-brad-pitt-quentin-tarantino-interview/ | title = Quentin Tarantino, Brad Pitt, and Leonardo DiCaprio Take You Inside 'Once Upon a Time...In Hollywood' | first = Michael | last = Hainey | date = May 21, 2019 | accessdate = January 19, 2020 | magazine = [[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] }}</ref> The life of the work for the first five years was as a novel,<ref name=\"esquire may2019\"/> which Tarantino considered to be an exploratory approach to the story he wanted to tell, not yet having decided if it would be a screenplay. Tarantino tried other writing approaches: the early scene between DiCaprio's Dalton and Pacino's Marvin Schwarz was originally written as a one-act play as part of this exploratory work.<ref name=\"gamespot inspiration\"/>\n\nTarantino discovered the centerpiece for the work in 2009 while filming a movie with an actor that had the same stunt double for 20 years. Even though there was nothing but a small bit for the stuntman to do, Tarantino was asked to use him, and he agreed. The relationship fascinated Tarantino and inspired him to make a film about Hollywood.<ref name=recut/> Tarantino said that while the stuntman may have been a perfect double for the actor years earlier, at the time he had come to meet them, \"this was maybe the last or second-to-last thing they'd be doing together\".<ref name=\"gamespot inspiration\">{{cite web | url = https://www.gamespot.com/articles/quentin-tarantino-reveals-inspiration-behind-once-/1100-6472880/ | title =Quentin Tarantino Reveals Inspiration Behind Once Upon A Time In Hollywood | first = James | last = O'Conner | date = January 19, 2020 | accessdate = January 19, 2020 | work = [[GameSpot]] }}</ref>\n\nTarantino first created Cliff Booth, giving him a massive backstory. Then, the actor Booth was the stunt double for Rick Dalton. Tarantino decided to have them be [[Sharon Tate]]'s next-door neighbors in 1969. The first plot point he developed was the ending, then moved backwards from there, this being the first time Tarantino had worked this way. He thought of doing an [[Elmore Leonard]]-type story, but realized he was confident enough in his characters to let them drive the film and let it be a day in the life of Booth, Dalton, and Tate. He would use sequences from Dalton's films for the action, inspired by [[Richard Rush (director)|Richard Rush]]'s ''[[The Stunt Man]]'', which used the scenes from the [[WWI]] movie they were making within the film as the action.<ref>{{cite podcast |last=Lattanzio |first=Ryan |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/08/quentin-tarantino-paul-thomas-anderson-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-podcast-1202168301 |title=Listen to Quentin Tarantino and Paul Thomas Anderson Talk 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' |website=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=September 5, 2019 |date=August 24, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829013436/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/08/quentin-tarantino-paul-thomas-anderson-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-podcast-1202168301/ |archivedate=August 29, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Further, to get his mind into the Dalton character, Tarantino wrote out five hypothetical episodes of the fictional television show ''Bounty Law'', in which Dalton had starred, having become fascinated with the amount of story crammed into half-hour episodes of 1950s western shows. Tarantino has expressed interest in turning these five scripts, as well as ideas for three more, into an actual ''Bounty Law'' television series in the future.<ref name=Tarantino-Deadline-Interview/>\n\n=== Pre-production ===\nOn July 11, 2017, it was announced that [[Quentin Tarantino]]'s next film would be about the [[Manson Family]] murders. [[Harvey Weinstein|Harvey]] and [[Bob Weinstein]] would be involved, but it was not known whether [[The Weinstein Company]] would distribute the film, as Tarantino sought to cast before sending out a package to studios. Tarantino approached [[Brad Pitt]] and [[Jennifer Lawrence]] to star in the film. It was reported that [[Margot Robbie]] was being considered for [[Sharon Tate]].<ref name=\"FirsReportedTHR\"/> [[Samuel L. Jackson]] was in talks for a major role, and Pitt was in talks for the detective investigating the murders.<ref name=\"FirsReportedDeadline\"/>\n\nAfter the [[Harvey Weinstein sexual abuse allegations]], Tarantino cut ties with Weinstein and sought a new distributor, after having worked with Weinstein for his entire career. At this point, [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] was revealed to be among a short list of actors Tarantino was considering for the film.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fleming Jr |first1=Mike |title=Quentin Tarantino Seeking New Movie Home: Studios Reading #9 This Week |url=https://deadline.com/2017/11/quentin-tarantino-new-home-studios-reading-number-9-harvey-weinstein-1202199806/ |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=November 8, 2017 |date=November 1, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108094853/http://deadline.com/2017/11/quentin-tarantino-new-home-studios-reading-number-9-harvey-weinstein-1202199806/|archive-date=November 8, 2017}}</ref> A short time later, reports circulated that studios were bidding for the film set in Los Angeles in the late 1960s, that [[Tom Cruise]] was in talks for one of the leads, and that [[David Heyman]] had joined as a producer, along with Tarantino and [[Shannon McIntosh (filmmaker)|Shannon McIntosh]].<ref name=\"HeymanProducer\"/>\n\nOn November 11, 2017, [[Sony Pictures]] announced they would distribute the film, beating [[Warner Bros.]], [[Universal Pictures]], [[Paramount Pictures]], [[Annapurna Pictures]] and [[Lionsgate]].<ref name=\"SonyWins\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/11/quentin-tarantino-sony-pictures-wins-auction-charles-manson-margot-robbie-tom-cruise-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-1202210597/ |title=Sony Pictures Confirms Quentin Tarantino Deal; Margot Robbie, Tom Cruise, Brad Pitt, Leonardo DiCaprio Circling |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |date=November 17, 2017 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618152249/https://deadline.com/2017/11/quentin-tarantino-sony-pictures-wins-auction-charles-manson-margot-robbie-tom-cruise-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-1202210597/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref> Tarantino's demands included a $95&nbsp;million budget, [[final cut privilege]], \"extraordinary creative controls\", 25% of [[first-dollar gross]],<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/how-sony-nabbed-quentin-tarantinos-manson-movie-1059742 |title=How Sony Nabbed Quentin Tarantino's Manson Movie |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=November 18, 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616205706/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/how-sony-nabbed-quentin-tarantinos-manson-movie-1059742|archive-date=June 16, 2018}}</ref> and the stipulation that the rights revert to him after 10 to 20 years.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n=== Casting ===\nIn January 2018, DiCaprio signed on, taking a pay cut to collaborate with Tarantino again.<ref name=\"DiCaprioCast\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/leonardo-dicaprio-quentin-tarantino-manson-movie-casting-1202241971/ |title=Leonardo DiCaprio To Star in Quentin Tarantino's New Movie |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |date=January 12, 2018 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175345/https://deadline.com/2018/01/leonardo-dicaprio-quentin-tarantino-manson-movie-casting-1202241971/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/celebrity-salaries-daniel-craig-jennifer-lawrence-leonardo-dicaprio-1202801717/ |title=Leonardo DiCaprio, Jennifer Lawrence and Other Star Salaries Revealed |last1=Lang |first1=Brent |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |date=May 8, 2018 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618152314/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/celebrity-salaries-daniel-craig-jennifer-lawrence-leonardo-dicaprio-1202801717/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref> [[Al Pacino]] was being considered for a role.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/leonardo-dicaprio-charles-manson-movie-quentin-tarantino-1202663081/ |title=Leonardo DiCaprio to Star in Quentin Tarantino's Manson Movie |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=January 12, 2018 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175635/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/leonardo-dicaprio-charles-manson-movie-quentin-tarantino-1202663081/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref> On February 28, 2018, the film was titled ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'', with Pitt cast in the role Cruise was also up for.<ref name=\"PittCast\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202306448/ |title=Quentin Tarantino Taps Brad Pitt To Join Leonardo DiCaprio In 'Once Upon A Time in Hollywood' |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |date=February 28, 2018 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620171241/https://deadline.com/2018/02/quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202306448/|archive-date=June 20, 2018}}</ref> DiCaprio and Pitt were each paid $10&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/celebrity-salaries-leonardo-dicaprio-margot-robbie-dwayne-johnson-will-smith-1203200508/ |title=Leonardo DiCaprio, Margot Robbie and More 2019 Star Salaries Revealed |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]| access-date=April 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501003157/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/celebrity-salaries-leonardo-dicaprio-margot-robbie-dwayne-johnson-will-smith-1203200508/ |archive-date=May 1, 2019|date=April 30, 2019 }}</ref> In March 2018, Robbie, who had expressed interest in working with Tarantino,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/margot-robbie-reliving-tonya-hardings-abuse-her-superhero-stalker-fears-1071169 |title=Margot Robbie on Reliving Tonya Harding's 'Abuse' and Her Superhero Stalker Fears |last=Rose |first=Lacey |date=January 4, 2018 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618130057/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/margot-robbie-reliving-tonya-hardings-abuse-her-superhero-stalker-fears-1071169|archive-date=June 18, 2018 |accessdate=June 18, 2018}}</ref> signed to co-star as Sharon Tate, while [[Zo\u00eb Bell]] confirmed she would appear.<ref name=\"RobbieCast\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/margot-robbie-sharon-tate-quentin-tarantino-film-leonardo-dicaprio-brad-pitt-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202336947/ |title=Margot Robbie Now in Negotiations To Play Sharon Tate in Quentin Tarantino Film |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |date=March 13, 2018 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618152319/https://deadline.com/2018/03/margot-robbie-sharon-tate-quentin-tarantino-film-leonardo-dicaprio-brad-pitt-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202336947/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"BellCast\">{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/03/zoe-bell-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-pitt-dicaprio-1201937156/ |title=Zo\u00eb Bell on Quentin Tarantino's New Movie: The World Is Going to Implode 'With So Much Genius in One Space' |last=Sharf |first=Zack |date=March 8, 2018 |work=[[IndieWire]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618125944/http://www.indiewire.com/2018/03/zoe-bell-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-pitt-dicaprio-1201937156/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/quentin-tarantinos-longtime-stuntwoman-says-shell-work-on-his-next-film-in-some-capacity-video/ |title=Zoe Bell to Work on Quentin Tarantino's 'Once upon a Time in Hollywood' |first=Jeremy |last=Fuster |date=March 7, 2018 |work=[[The Wrap]] |accessdate=March 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180308030601/https://www.thewrap.com/quentin-tarantinos-longtime-stuntwoman-says-shell-work-on-his-next-film-in-some-capacity-video/|archive-date=March 8, 2018}}</ref> In April 2018, [[Jessica Lange]] was in talks to play Mary Alice Schwarzs, but dropped out and [[Brenda Vaccaro]] replaced her. In May 2018, [[Burt Reynolds]], [[Tim Roth]], [[Kurt Russell]], and [[Michael Madsen]] joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/quentin-tarantino-burt-reynolds-george-spahn-manson-ranch-owner-tim-roth-kurt-russell-michael-madsen-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-sony-1202385014/ |title=Quentin Tarantino Cast Thickens: Burt Reynolds To Star, Roth, Russell, Madsen Play Small Roles; Margot Robbie Confirmed As Sharon Tate |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |date=May 8, 2018 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615114939/https://deadline.com/2018/05/quentin-tarantino-burt-reynolds-george-spahn-manson-ranch-owner-tim-roth-kurt-russell-michael-madsen-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-sony-1202385014/|archive-date=June 15, 2018}}</ref> [[Timothy Olyphant]] was also cast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/timothy-olyphant-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202388439/ |title=Timothy Olyphant Negotiating Lead Role in Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time in Hollywood' |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |date=May 11, 2018 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175226/https://deadline.com/2018/05/timothy-olyphant-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202388439/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref> In June 2018, [[Damian Lewis]], [[Luke Perry]], [[Emile Hirsch]], [[Dakota Fanning]], [[Clifton Collins Jr.]], Keith Jefferson, [[Nicholas Hammond]], Pacino, and [[Scoot McNairy]] joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-damian-lewis-luke-perry-dakota-fanning-cast-1202405007/ |title=Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time in Hollywood' Adds Luke Perry, Damian Lewis, Dakota Fanning, More |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |date=June 6, 2018 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614011100/https://deadline.com/2018/06/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-damian-lewis-luke-perry-dakota-fanning-cast-1202405007/|archive-date=June 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/al-pacino-quentin-tarantino-manson-movie-1202826780/ |title=Al Pacino Joins Quentin Tarantino's Manson Movie (Exclusive) |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=June 7, 2018 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618103114/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/al-pacino-quentin-tarantino-manson-movie-1202826780/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/scoot-mcnairy-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-leonardo-dicaprio-brad-pitt-margot-robbie-1202415237/ |title=Scoot McNairy Joins Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time in Hollywood' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=June 21, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621221411/https://deadline.com/2018/06/scoot-mcnairy-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-leonardo-dicaprio-brad-pitt-margot-robbie-1202415237/ |archive-date=June 21, 2018|date=June 21, 2018 }}</ref> [[Spencer Garrett]], [[James Remar]], Brenda Vaccaro, and [[Mike Moh]] were announced in July.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/quentin-tarantino-rounds-out-cast-with-spencer-garrett-martin-kove-james-remar-brenda-vaccaro-1202424049/ |title=Quentin Tarantino Rounds Out Cast With Spencer Garrett, Martin Kove, James Remar, Brenda Vaccaro |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]| access-date=July 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711035552/https://deadline.com/2018/07/quentin-tarantino-rounds-out-cast-with-spencer-garrett-martin-kove-james-remar-brenda-vaccaro-1202424049/ |archive-date=July 11, 2018|date=July 10, 2018}}</ref> In August 2018, [[Damon Herriman]] as [[Charles Manson]], and [[Lena Dunham]], [[Austin Butler]], [[Danny Strong]], [[Rumer Willis]], [[Dreama Walker]], and [[Margaret Qualley]] were cast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/lena-dunham-austin-butler-maya-hawke-lorenza-izzo-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202450671/ |title=Lena Dunham, Austin Butler, Maya Hawke, Lorenza Izzo Board Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time in Hollywood' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Amanda |last=N'Duka |date=August 22, 2018 |accessdate=August 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180823042113/https://deadline.com/2018/08/lena-dunham-austin-butler-maya-hawke-lorenza-izzo-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-1202450671/|archive-date=August 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/08/22/lena-dunham-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/ |title=Lena Dunham to play Manson disciple in Tarantino's Once Upon A Time in Hollywood |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |first=Piya |last=Sinha-Roy |date=August 22, 2018 |accessdate=August 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180823031438/https://ew.com/movies/2018/08/22/lena-dunham-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/|archive-date=August 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/danny-strong-sydney-sweeney-join-once-a-time-hollywood-1129521 |title=Danny Strong, Sydney Sweeney Join 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' (Exclusive) |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |first=Mia |last=Galuppo |date=August 27, 2018 |accessdate=August 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828035848/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/danny-strong-sydney-sweeney-join-once-a-time-hollywood-1129521|archive-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/charles-manson-damon-herriman-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-time-hollywood-rumer-willis/ |title='Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Adds Rumer Willis, Margaret Qualley and Damon Herriman (Exclusive) |access-date=August 29, 2018 |website=[[TheWrap]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829110013/https://www.thewrap.com/charles-manson-damon-herriman-quentin-tarantino-once-upon-time-hollywood-rumer-willis/ |archive-date=August 29, 2018|date=August 29, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nWhen casting the leads, Tarantino invited Pitt, DiCaprio, and Robbie to his house to read the only copy of the full script, to prevent leaks. When Butler auditioned, he did not know which character it was for. Tarantino told him it was for a villain or a hero on ''Lancer'', when in fact it was for [[Tex Watson|\"Tex\" Watson]]. To prepare for her audition, [[Maya Hawke]] practiced with her father, [[Ethan Hawke]]. She said the process was unlike any other except maybe auditioning for drama school, and during it they worked on the scene in many different ways, with different combinations of people. Willis auditioned for two roles, neither of which she got, then was offered the part of [[Joanna Pettet]]. [[Sydney Sweeney]] said everyone she auditioned with did so for the same character, then were told they could do extra credit. Some did artwork, and she wrote a letter in character. [[Julia Butters]] says her sitcom ''[[American Housewife]]'' was on while Tarantino was writing her character, Trudi Fraser. He looked up and said, \"Maybe she can try this.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Gardner |first=Chris |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/quentin-tarantinos-once-a-time-hollywood-manson-family-actors-detail-unconventional-audition-process-1226543 |title=\"Once Upon a Time in Hollywood\" Actors Detail Quentin Tarantino's \"Unconventional\" Prcoess |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=September 4, 2019 |date=July 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190731051119/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/quentin-tarantinos-once-a-time-hollywood-manson-family-actors-detail-unconventional-audition-process-1226543 |archive-date=July 31, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming and design ===\n[[Principal photography]] began on June 18, 2018, in Los Angeles, California, and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] on November 1, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://omegaunderground.com/2018/05/24/tarantinos-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-begins-filming-on-june-18th-in-la/ |title=Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time in Hollywood' Begins Filming on June 18th in LA |last=Marc |first=Christopher |date=May 24, 2018 |website=Omega Underground |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618125719/https://omegaunderground.com/2018/05/24/tarantinos-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-begins-filming-on-june-18th-in-la/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.backstage.com/resources/detail/productionlisting/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-86666/ |title=Once Upon a Time in Hollywood |website=[[Backstage (magazine)|Backstage]] |accessdate=November 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322012929/https://www.backstage.com/resources/detail/productionlisting/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-86666/|archive-date=March 22, 2019}}</ref> Reynolds died in September 2018 before filming any of his scenes; [[Bruce Dern]] was cast as [[George Spahn]] in his place.<ref name=\"Dern\"/>\n\nTarantino's directive was to turn Los Angeles of 2018 into Los Angeles of 1969 without [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]].<ref name=\"afar\"/> For this, Tarantino tapped into previous collaborators for production: editor [[Fred Raskin]], cinematographer [[Robert Richardson (cinematographer)|Robert Richardson]], sound editor [[Wylie Stateman]] and makeup artist Heba Thorisdottir. He also brought first-time collaborators production designer Barbara Ling based on her work in recreating historical settings in ''[[The Doors (film)|The Doors]]'', and costume designer [[Arianne Phillips]], who had a strong client list to her name including [[Tom Ford]], [[James Mangold]] and [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]].<ref name=\"variety making 60s\">{{cite web | url = https://variety.com/2020/artisans/production/quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-2-1203484354/ | title = Quentin Tarantino on Re-Creating 1960s L.A. for 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' | first = Jazz | last = Tangcay | date = January 29, 2020 | accessdate = January 29, 2020 | work = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] }}</ref> Production and filming required months of collaboration with city planners, business owners, set decorators, and construction crews. While filming at [[Musso & Frank Grill]], the owners brought out the original plates.\n\nTo film at the Pussycat Theater, production designer Barbara Ling and her team covered the building's [[LED]] signage and reattached the theater's iconic logo, rebuilding the letters and neon. Ling said the lettering on every marquee in the film is historically accurate. To restore Larry Edmund's Bookshop, she reproduced the original storefront sign and tracked down period-appropriate merchandise, even recreating book covers. For the Bruin and Fox Village theaters Ling's team restored the theaters, their marquees, and the storefronts around them. Stan's Donuts, across the street from the Bruin got a complete makeover.<ref name=\"afar\">{{cite news |last=Wakim |first=Marielle |url=https://www.afar.com/magazine/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-filming-locations-you-can-visit-in-los-angeles |title='Once Upon a Time... in Hollywood' Filming Locations You Can Visit in Los Angeles |website=[[Afar (magazine)|Afar]] |access-date=September 2, 2019 |date=July 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190903051130/https://www.afar.com/magazine/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-filming-locations-you-can-visit-in-los-angeles |archive-date=September 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nTarantino was adamant about filming at the real [[Playboy Mansion]], but it took a long time to obtain permission since by the time of pre-production the mansion had been sold to a private owner following [[Hugh Hefner]]'s death. Tarantino and Ling met with the new owner to discuss their plans and the parts of the property which they wanted to use. After long negotiations the owner agreed, and Ling was able to dress the vacant mansion, front courtyard, and backyard for the party scene, evoking as much of the 1960s appearance of the mansion as possible.<ref name=recreating-Hollywood/>\n\nFor ''Bounty Law'', Ling went for a dusty, dirty, early ''[[Deadwood (TV series)|Deadwood]]'' look. Ling's team found one of the last great living Italian artists to do two of the film's posters. Other posters used and the mugs, are part of Tarantino's personal collection. Movie poster artist [[Steven Chorney]] created the poster for the film, as a reference to ''[[The Mod Squad]]''. He also created the posters for ''Nebraska Jim'', ''Operation Dyn-O-Mite'', ''Uccidimi Subito Ringo Disse il Gringo'', ''Hell-Fire Texas'', and ''Comanche Uprising'', which was reprinted for Dalton's home parking spot. [[Mad (magazine)|''Mad'']] magazine caricaturist [[Tom Richmond (illustrator)|Tom Richmond]] created the covers of ''Mad'' and ''[[TV Guide]]'' featuring Dalton's Jake Cahill. Spahn Ranch was recreated in detail over about a three-month period. The [[Playboy Mansion]] scene was shot at the actual mansion.<ref name=recreating-hollywood/><ref>{{cite web |last=Combemale |first=Leslie |url=https://www.mpaa.org/2019/08/artist-steve-chorney-on-crafting-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywoods-poster-more/ |title=Artist Steve Chorney on Crafting ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood''{{'}}s Poster & More |website=[[Motion Picture Association of America]]| access-date=September 8, 2019 |date=August 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Minow |first=Nell |url=https://www.mpaa.org/2019/08/meet-the-caricaturist-who-created-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywoods-classic-mad-magazine-cover/ |title=Meet the Caricaturist who Created 'Once Upon a Time in... Hollywood's' Classic MAD Magazine Cover |website=[[Motion Picture Association of America]]| access-date=September 8, 2019 |date=August 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nTarantino told cinematographer [[Robert Richardson (cinematographer)|Robert Richardson]], \"I want it to feel retro but I want it to be contemporary.\" Richardson shot in [[Kodak]] [[35 mm movie film|35mm]] with [[Panavision]] cameras and lenses, in order to weave time periods. For ''Bounty Law'' they shot in black and white, and brief sequences in [[Super 8 film|Super 8]] and [[16mm]] [[Ektachrome]]. In the film, ''[[Lancer (TV series)|Lancer]]'' was shot on a retrofitted Western Street backlot at [[Universal Studios]], designed by Ling. Richardson crossed ''Lancer'' with ''[[Alias Smith and Jones]]'' for the retro-future look Tarantino wanted. The way they filmed ''Lancer'' was not possible in 1969, but Tarantino wanted his personal touch on it. Richardson said that filming the movie touched him personally, \"The film speaks to all of us... We are all fragile beings with a limited time to achieve whatever it is we desire... that at any moment that place will shift... So take stock in life and have the courage to believe in yourself.\"<ref name=recreating-hollywood>{{cite web |last=Han |first=Karen |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/7/28/8932339/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-playboy-mansion |title=What it took to get the Playboy Mansion for Once Upon a Time... in Hollywood |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |access-date=September 3, 2019 |date=July 28, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906142247/https://www.polygon.com/2019/7/28/8932339/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-playboy-mansion |archive-date=September 6, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Desowitz |first=Bill |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-cinematographer-robert-richardson-quentin-tarantino-1969-1202159937/ |title=\"Once Upon a Time in Hollywood\": How Cinematographer Robert Richardson captured 1969 in 2019 |website=[[IndieWire]] |access-date=September 3, 2019 |date=July 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723131120/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-cinematographer-robert-richardson-quentin-tarantino-1969-1202159937/ |archive-date=July 23, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe exterior of the Van Nuys drive-in scene was filmed at the Paramount Theater since the Van Nuys Theater no longer exists. As the camera rises up over the theater, the shot transitions to a miniature set with toy cars.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2477166/cool-tricks-quentin-tarantino-used-to-recreate-1969-la-for-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood| title=Cool Tricks Quentin Tarantino Used to Recreate 1969 L.A. For Once Upon a Time in Hollywood| date=July 26, 2019| access-date=November 9, 2019|publisher=CinemaBlend| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109202340/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2477166/cool-tricks-quentin-tarantino-used-to-recreate-1969-la-for-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood| archive-date=November 9, 2019| url-status=live}}</ref> For some of the driving scenes, Los Angeles freeways were shut down for hours in order to fill them with vintage cars.<ref name=cinema-blend/>\n\n== Music ==\n=== Soundtrack ===\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Once Upon a Time in Hollywood (soundtrack)\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = Various Artists\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2019\n| recorded     = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Rock and roll]]\n| length       = \n| label        = [[Columbia Records]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[The Hateful Eight (soundtrack)|The Hateful Eight]]\n| prev_year    = 2015\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| chronology   = [[Quentin Tarantino]] film soundtrack\n}}\n'''''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood''''' is also the name of the soundtrack. [[Pitchfork (website)|''Pitchfork'']] said the music was \"a highlight\" and an \"oft-disquieting mixtape of golden-age [[rock n' roll]], radio DJ patter, and period-specific commercials.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/various-artists-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/ |title=Various Artists: Once Upon a Time in ... Hollywood (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) |website=Pitchfork |language=en |access-date=August 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815202640/https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/various-artists-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/ |archive-date=August 15, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/film/2019-08-14/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-soundtrack-here-are-all-the-1960s-tunes-featured-in-the-movie/ |title=Once Upon A Time In Hollywood soundtrack: All the 1960s tunes featured in the movie |website=[[Radio Times]] |language=en |access-date=August 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815202637/https://www.radiotimes.com/news/film/2019-08-14/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-soundtrack-here-are-all-the-1960s-tunes-featured-in-the-movie/ |archive-date=August 15, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>[[File:Paul Revere and the Raiders 1967.JPG|thumb|upright|The soundtrack includes three songs by [[Paul Revere & the Raiders]]]]\n\n==== Track listing ====\n# \"[[Treat Her Right (Roy Head song)|Treat Her Right]]\" \u2013 [[Roy Head]] and the Traits\n# \"[[Ramblin' Gamblin' Man (song)|Ramblin' Gamblin' Man]]\" \u2013 [[Bob Seger]] System\n# \"[[Hush (Deep Purple song)|Hush]]\" \u2013 [[Deep Purple]]\n# \"Hector\" \u2013 The Village Callers\n# \"Son of a Lovin' Man\" \u2013 [[Buchanan Brothers]]\n# \"Paxton Quigley's Had the Course\" \u2013 [[Chad & Jeremy]]\n# \"Hungry\" \u2013 [[Paul Revere & the Raiders]]\n# \"Good Thing\" \u2013 Paul Revere & the Raiders\n# \"Choo Choo Train\" \u2013 [[The Box Tops]]\n# \"Jenny Take a Ride\" \u2013 [[Mitch Ryder]] & [[the Detroit Wheels]]\n# \"[[Kentucky Woman#Deep Purple cover|Kentucky Woman]]\" \u2013 Deep Purple\n# \"The Circle Game\" \u2013 [[Buffy Sainte-Marie]]\n# \"[[Mrs. Robinson]]\" \u2013 [[Simon & Garfunkel]]\n# \"[[Bring a Little Lovin'#In popular culture|Bring a Little Lovin']]\" \u2013 [[Los Bravos]]\n# \"Hey Little Girl\" \u2013 [[Dee Clark]]\n# \"[[Brother Love's Travelling Salvation Show (song)|Brother Love's Traveling Salvation Show]]\" \u2013 [[Neil Diamond]]\n# \"Don't Chase Me Around\" \u2013 [[Robert Corff]]\n# \"[[Mr. Sun, Mr. Moon]]\" (feat. [[Mark Lindsay]]) \u2013 Paul Revere & the Raiders\n# \"[[California Dreamin'#Lesser-known versions|California Dreamin']]\" \u2013 [[Jos\u00e9 Feliciano